body:
Here a minimal example: 

``` verilog
module bsp_e(a, z);
    output z;
    input  a;
    wire s1;
assign
    s1 = ~a,
    z = s1;
endmodule
```

After executing the following skript: 

```
read_verilog ../examples/bsp_e.v
proc; opt; fsm; opt; memory; opt
techmap; opt
dfflibmap -liberty ../libraries/yosys/mycells.lib
abc -liberty ../libraries/yosys/mycells.lib
clean
write_verilog -noattr ../tmp.v
```

I get the following output:

``` verilog
module bsp_e(a, z);
  input a;
  wire s1;
  output z;
  YNOT _0_ (
    .A(a),
    .Y(z)
  );
  assign s1 = z; /* this is reversed */
endmodule
```

I pinned it down to opt_clean reversing the assignments.
This happens with commit b226893461af46f2183be8ca9dfab62b49133c71
